========================================================================
KEY ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS
========================================================================

- MPAS stream manager only supports nCells/nEdges/nVertices decomposed
  dims. Remapped (lon,lat) output MUST bypass stream manager via direct
  PIO. This is by design, not a workaround.

- Remapped filenames derived from native stream's filename_template via
  MPAS_stream_mgr_get_property. Inserts ".remapped" before ".nc".

- File rotation: register_var stores metadata at init, check_rotate
  opens/closes files on date boundary, replays var defs automatically.

- EAM remap is transparent: horiz_remap_file(tape) replaces data in
  cam_history at write time. Same filename, same tape.

